      <section class="left-column">
        <h2>Job Description</h2>
        <p>
          We are seeking a skilled and proactive DevOps Engineer to join our engineering team.
          In this role, you will be responsible for building, automating, and maintaining scalable
          infrastructure and deployment pipelines that support reliable and efficient software delivery.
        </p>
        <p>
          You will collaborate closely with development, QA, and operations teams to improve system
          performance, enhance deployment processes, and ensure high availability of applications.
          The ideal candidate has strong automation skills, a problem‑solving mindset, and experience
          working in fast‑paced Agile environments.
        </p>

        <h3>Responsibilities</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines for automated build, test, and deployment.</li>
          <li>Manage and optimize cloud infrastructure (AWS, Azure, or GCP).</li>
          <li>Automate infrastructure provisioning using Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools.</li>
          <li>Monitor system performance, availability, and security.</li>
          <li>Ensure application scalability, reliability, and high availability.</li>
          <li>Collaborate with development teams to improve deployment strategies.</li>
          <li>Troubleshoot production issues and implement preventive solutions.</li>
          <li>Maintain documentation for DevOps processes and infrastructure.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Strong experience in DevOps tools and practices.</li>
          <li>Hands‑on experience with CI/CD tools (Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, etc.).</li>
          <li>Experience with cloud platforms (AWS / Azure / GCP).</li>
          <li>Proficiency in Docker and containerization.</li>
          <li>Knowledge of Kubernetes or other container orchestration tools.</li>
          <li>Experience with Linux administration and shell scripting.</li>
          <li>Familiarity with version control systems (Git).</li>
          <li>Understanding of Agile and DevOps methodologies.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

